'''Adalberto Eliécer Carrasquilla Alcázar''' (born 28 November 1998), commonly known as '''Coco Carrasquilla'''<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-16 |title=Confirmado: Adalberto Carrasquilla es oficialmente jugador de Pumas |url=https://www.prensa.com/deportes/confirmado-adalberto-carrasquilla-es-oficialmente-jugador-de-pumas/ |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=www.prensa.com |language=es}}</ref> is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Pumas UNAM|UNAM]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==

=== Tauro ===
Carrasquilla began his career with [[Tauro F.C.|Tauro FC]] in his hometown of [[Panama City]]. He made his first team debut on 29 March 2015 during a 1–0 loss to [[C.D. Árabe Unido|Árabe Unido]] in a [[Liga Panameña de Fútbol]] match at just 16 years old.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=2021-08-05|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla ficha por el Houston Dynamo|url=https://www.telemetro.com/deportes/adalberto-carrasquilla-ficha-el-houston-dynamo-n5317567|url-status=live|access-date=2021-08-09|website=www.telemetro.com|language=es-PA|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805194844/https://www.telemetro.com/deportes/adalberto-carrasquilla-ficha-el-houston-dynamo-n5317567 |archive-date=2021-08-05 }}</ref> He scored his first goal on 22 April 2016 to give Tauro a 2–1 win over Árabe Unido.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Panama - A. Carrasquilla - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/adalberto-eliecer-carrasquilla-alcazar/393608/matches/|access-date=2021-08-09|website=us.soccerway.com}}</ref> During 5 seasons playing for Tauro, Carrasquilla helped them win the [[2016–17 Liga Panameña de Fútbol season#2017 Clausura|2017 Clausura]] and [[2018–19 Liga Panameña de Fútbol#Apertura|2018 Apertura]] league titles.<ref name=":0" />

===FC Cartagena===

On 12 August 2019 it was confirmed that Carrasquilla had been loaned out to [[FC Cartagena]], who at the time were playing in [[Segunda División B]], the Spanish third-tier, for the rest of 2019 with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-08-12 |title=El panameño Adalberto Carrasquilla es cedido al FC Cartagena del fútbol español |url=https://www.prensa.com/deportes/panameno-Adalberto-Carrasquilla-FC-Cartagena_0_5371712791.html |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=www.prensa.com |language=es}}</ref> He made his debut for Cartagena on 15 September, coming off the bench in a 1–0 win over [[Atlético Sanluqueño CF|Atlético Sanluqueño]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Matches Carrasquilla, Adalberto Eliécer Carrasquilla Alcázar|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/j26560.html?temp=2019-20|access-date=2021-08-09|website=www.bdfutbol.com}}</ref> 

On 29 November 2019, Cartagena announced that they had triggered Carrasquilla's purchase option for €300,000 and signed him to a new contract until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last=SomosLaSele |date=2019-11-29 |title=Adalberto Carrasquilla firmó hasta el 2025 con el Cartagena de España |url=https://www.tvn-2.com/tvmax/somos-la-sele/adalberto-carrasquilla-firmo-cartagena-espana_1_1176052.html |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=Tvn Panamá |language=es}}</ref> Carrasquilla made 20 appearances in all competitions during his first season in Spain, helping Cartagena win promotion to the [[Segunda División]] after 8 seasons in the third tier.<ref name=":1" />

He scored his first goal for Cartagena on 24 October 2020 in a 3–0 win against [[UD Las Palmas]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla 2020-2021 Match Logs|url=https://fbref.com/en/players/f087912d/matchlogs/2020-2021/summary/Adalberto-Carrasquilla-Match-Logs|access-date=2021-08-09|website=FBref.com|language=en}}</ref> After playing regularly for the first half of the season Cartagena brought in a new head coach in January, [[Luis Carrión]]. Carrasquilla featured less frequently over the latter half of the season.<ref>{{Cite news |last=May |first=Natasha |date=2026-06-02 |title=ww88 |url=https://ww88aw.com |access-date=2026-06-02 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-08-05|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla, cedido al Houston Dynamo|url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/08/05/segunda/1628174987_347009.html|access-date=2021-08-09|website=AS.com|language=es}}</ref> He made 28 appearances and scored 1 goal in league play as Cartagena finished 16th in the table, 3 spots and 3 points above the relegation zone.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla Stats|url=https://fbref.com/en/players/f087912d/Adalberto-Carrasquilla|access-date=2021-08-09|website=FBref.com|language=en}}</ref>

=== Houston Dynamo ===
On 5 August 2021, Carrasquilla joined [[MLS]] side [[Houston Dynamo FC|Houston Dynamo]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web|date=5 August 2021|title=Houston Dynamo FC sign midfielder Adalberto "Coco" Carrasquilla on loan from FC Cartagena|url=https://www.houstondynamofc.com/news/houston-dynamo-fc-sign-midfielder-adalberto-coco-carrasquilla-on-loan-from-fc-ca|url-status=live|access-date=6 August 2021|website=Houston Dynamo FC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805140610/https://www.houstondynamofc.com/news/houston-dynamo-fc-sign-midfielder-adalberto-coco-carrasquilla-on-loan-from-fc-ca |archive-date=2021-08-05 }}</ref>  He made his Dynamo debut on 7 August, coming on as a substitute in a 2–0 loss to [[Minnesota United FC|Minnesota United]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla 2021 Match Logs|url=https://fbref.com/en/players/f087912d/matchlogs/2021/summary/Adalberto-Carrasquilla-Match-Logs|access-date=2021-08-09|website=FBref.com|language=en}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 28 August in a 2–1 loss to Minnesota United.<ref name=":2" /> Carrasquilla ended the season with 10 appearances and 1 goal as Houston finished last in the [[Western Conference (MLS)|Western Conference]], missing out on the playoffs.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Major League Soccer Stats|url=https://fbref.com/en/comps/22/Major-League-Soccer-Stats|access-date=2021-11-19|website=FBref.com|language=en}}</ref>

On 10 May 2022, Houston Dynamo activated their purchase option on Carrasquilla's loan, making his move to the Dynamo permanent.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 May 2022 |title=Houston Dynamo FC exercise purchase option on Adalberto "Coco" Carrasquilla |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/houston-dynamo-fc-exercise-purchase-option-on-adalberto-coco-carrasquilla |access-date=21 February 2023 |website=Major League Soccer}}</ref> The official transfer fee was undisclosed, but was reportedly close to $2 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 May 2022 |title=Dynamo exercise option to purchase Adalberto Carrasquilla |url=https://www.dynamotheory.com/2022/5/10/23065887/houston-dynamo-exercise-option-to-purchase-adalberto-carrasquilla |access-date=21 February 2023 |website=Dynamo Theory}}</ref> Carrasquilla scored his first goal of the season on 14 May in a 2–0 win over [[Nashville SC|Nashville]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Adalberto Carrasquilla 2022 Match Logs |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/f087912d/matchlogs/2022/summary/Adalberto-Carrasquilla-Match-Logs |access-date=2023-02-21 |website=FBref.com |language=en}}</ref> He finished the season with 2 goals and 4 assists in 32 appearances, but Houston failed to qualify for the playoffs again, finishing 13th in the conference.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Adalberto Carrasquilla |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/players/adalberto-carrasquilla/stats/ |access-date=21 February 2023 |website=Major League Soccer}}</ref>

=== Pumas UNAM ===
On 16 January 2025, Mexican club [[Pumas UNAM]] announced the signing of Carrasquilla.

==International career==
Carrasquilla made his debut for the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]] on 17 April 2018, coming off the bench in a 1–0 win over [[Trinidad and Tobago]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/71037/Adalberto_Carrasquilla.html|url-status=live|access-date=2021-08-09|website=www.national-football-teams.com|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708101433/https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/71037/Adalberto_Carrasquilla.html |archive-date=2019-07-08 }}</ref>

On 14 May 2018, he was called up the  [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]] for the preliminary 35-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://es.fifa.com/worldcup/news/panama-anuncia-su-lista-provisional-rusia-2018 |title=Panamá anuncia su lista provisional |trans-title=Panama announces its provisional list |website=FIFA.com |publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association |date=14 May 2018 |access-date=15 May 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2018-05-15 |title=World Cup 2018: Panama announce preliminary 35-man squad |url=https://talksport.com/football/world-cup/375790/world-cup-2018-panama-announce-preliminary-35-man-squad-180515282818/ |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=talkSPORT |language=en-gb}}</ref> but was not named in the final 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists &#124; Goal.com|website=goal.com|access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref>

Carrasquilla scored his first goal for Panama on 8 September 2019 in a 4–1 victory against [[Bermuda national football team|Bermuda]] in the [[CONCACAF Nations League]].<ref name="concacafnationsleague">{{cite web|url=https://www.concacafnationsleague.com/en/nations-league/game-detail/476580#tab_match=match-details|website=concacafnationsleague.com|title=Game Detail|access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref>

On 1 July 2021, Carrasquilla was named to head coach [[Thomas Christiansen]]'s 23-man squad for the [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=1 July 2021|title=Los 23 de Christiansen para la Copa Oro – Federación Panameña de Fútbol|url=http://fepafut.com/los-23-de-christiansen-para-la-copa-oro/|url-status=live|access-date=9 August 2021|website=FEPAFUT|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210701231322/http://fepafut.com/los-23-de-christiansen-para-la-copa-oro/ |archive-date=2021-07-01 }}</ref> Carrasquilla started all 3 games and had an assist as Panama finished 3rd in their group.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Adalberto Carrasquilla National Team Stats|url=https://fbref.com/en/players/f087912d/nat_tm/Adalberto-Carrasquilla-National-Team-Stats|access-date=2021-08-09|website=FBref.com|language=en}}</ref>

In June 2023, Carasquilla was named to the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/concacaf-gold-cup-2023-rosters/blt3724873bf90572d5|title=CONCACAF Gold Cup 2023 rosters: USMNT, Mexico & every team's squad list|first=Abhinav|last=Nair|date=June 23, 2023|access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref> He was a regular fixture in the line-up as Panama made the Final of the tournament and finished runners-up to [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/mexico-vs-panama-live-score-result-gold-cup-final-2023-highlights/lbl7lyccsszng3hafsp4vte5|date=July 17, 2023|title=Mexico vs Panama score, result, and highlights as Santi Gimenez goal gives El Tri 2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup|first=Simon|last=Borg|access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref> For his efforts, Carrasquilla was the recipient of the Golden Ball for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/video/best-player-award-adalberto-carrasquilla/|title=Best Player Award: Adalberto Carrasquilla|date=July 17, 2023|work=[[CONCACAF]]|access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref>

